msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix-01-faq.md:127 f2a8a80e8cab4212be24c8993c51ce25
msgid ""
"See the **Release Process** section in [08-build.md](08-build.md). In "
"short:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix-01-faq.md:133 4ba8f2334847486294ba1e4ec4211db3
msgid "Q: The CI build failed — do I need a new tag?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix-01-faq.md:135 8897ad461a1b4d0f953cf30ee24c106d
msgid ""
"Not necessarily. If the code is correct and it was a transient CI "
"failure, you can re-run the failed jobs from the GitHub Actions UI. See "
"[08-build.md](08-build.md) for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix-01-faq.md:137 582501d0f8434e60b78d736e5fc4b141
msgid "Q: How do I build for a different platform?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../appendix-01-faq.md:139 a9388064f9dc4268ab0fe725d6af1be3
msgid ""
"Cross-compilation for Tauri desktop apps is not straightforward. The "
"recommended approach is to build on the target platform (or use CI with a"
" build matrix). The GitHub Actions release workflow already covers macOS "
"(ARM + Intel), Linux, and Windows."
msgstr ""

